cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on the problem of curve detection in images. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes local fractal analysis and a CNN model, which suggests that it could potentially fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
